y, and optionally binds tokens to specific pods, secrets, or nodes. The LegacyClaims() function provides backward compatibility for legacy secret-based tokens. Both claim types are used by generateTokenIfNeeded() to create the actual JWT token string stored in the secret.\n\nPOD SPEC VALIDATION: The automountServiceAccountToken field is defined in pkg/apis/core/types.go for both PodSpec (allowing per-pod override) and ServiceAccount (setting namespace-wide default). The admission controller's Validate() method also enforces that pods have a valid service account reference and validates secret references based on the service account's mounted secrets list.\n\nThe complete pipeline ensures that: (1) pods automatically receive mounted service account tokens unless explicitly disabled, (2) tokens are stored as Kubernetes secrets, (3) token data is generated and managed automatically, and (4) service accounts exist in all namespaces."
